[00:35.81] Michelangelo lay on the scaffold high
[00:51.28] With paint in his beard and dust in his eye
[01:05.21] He chipped at the marble to find the vein
[01:12.71] He bargained with God through the physical pain
[01:21.90] But I sit slouched in an ergonomic chair
[01:28.49] Blue light bathing my thinning hair
[01:35.81] No callus on finger, no stain on the smock
[01:42.53] Just waiting for the render... watching the clock
[01:51.43] This is the Sistine Simulation
[01:59.31] A cathedral built on calculation
[02:06.35] I reach out my hand to the Adam I made
[02:13.23] But the image dissolves, and the pixels fade
[02:22.62] There is no spark, no divine ignition
[02:30.88] Just a hollow, high-res apparition
[02:37.35] I asked for the beauty of sixteen-twelve
[02:44.56] I told the machine to deeply delve
[02:52.58] It gave me the colors, the shadow, the light
[03:00.23] But something within it is not quite right
[03:08.44] Look at the fingers, look at the skin
[03:12.13] The eyes are too empty, the mouth is too thin
[03:15.71] I summoned a David from noise and from static
[03:19.19] But he has no soul... only mathematics
[03:23.68] I am not a creator. I am a requester
[03:30.24] I am a tourist in the gallery of my own imagination
[03:34.14] I type "Style of Da Vinci"
[03:37.62] And I steal the ghost of a dead man's hand
[03:41.40] To paint a world I do not understand
[04:48.29] This is the Sistine Simulation
[04:55.49] A cathedral built on calculation
[05:02.86] I reach out my hand to the Adam I made
[05:09.85] But the image dissolves, and the pixels fade
[05:19.31] There is no spark, no divine ignition
[05:26.77] Just a hollow, high-res apparition
[05:33.58] The fingers... They never touch
[05:50.11] They never touch. Glitch